<h2>Google API Keys</h2>
<p>In order to use the Google API, you will need to create two separate API keys. The <strong>server key</strong> handles API calls made from the back-end, whereas the <strong>browser key</strong> handles API calls made from the front-end. For full details, please consult the documentation regarding <a href="{{ docs }}/getting-started/api-keys/" target="_blank">Google Maps API keys</a>.</p>
{% include autosuggest with {
    config: {
        label: "Google API Server Key"|t('google-maps'),
        instructions: "Required for performing address lookups."|t('google-maps'),
        name: 'googleApiServerKey',
        required: true
    }
} %}
{% include autosuggest with {
    config: {
        label: "Google API Browser Key"|t('google-maps'),
        instructions: "Required for rendering static & dynamic maps."|t('google-maps'),
        name: 'googleApiBrowserKey',
        required: true
    }
} %}

<hr>

<h2>Visitor Geolocation</h2>
<p>You can use a third-party service to provide geolocation for your visitors, based on their detected IP address. IP-based geolocation is generally accurate to within a few miles/kilometers, which will be sufficient for the majority of purposes. For more information, please check out the complete documentation on <a href="{{ docs }}/geolocation/" target="_blank">Visitor Geolocation</a>.</p>
{% include dropdown with {
    attr: [
        'onchange="updateGeolocationService()"'
    ],
    config: {
        label: "Geolocation Service"|t('google-maps'),
        id: 'geolocation-service',
        name: 'geolocationService',
        instructions: "Select which third-party service will be providing geolocation results. [See full description of options...]({docs}/geolocation/service-providers/)"|t('google-maps', {'docs':docs}),
        value: settings.geolocationService ?? '',
        options: [
            { value: '',        label: 'None'|t('google-maps') },
            { value: 'ipstack', label: 'ipstack' },
            { value: 'maxmind', label: 'MaxMind' },
        ],
    }
} %}

<div id="ipstack" class="pane" style="display:none">
    <h2>ipstack Settings</h2>
    <p style="font-style: italic">Required if using the ipstack geolocation service.</p>
    {% include autosuggest with {
        config: {
            label: "API Access Key"|t,
            name: 'ipstackApiAccessKey',
        }
    } %}
</div>

<div id="maxmind" class="pane" style="display:none">
    <h2>MaxMind Settings</h2>
    <p style="font-style: italic">Required if using the MaxMind geolocation service.</p>
    {% include autosuggest with {
        config: {
            label: "User ID"|t('google-maps'),
            name: 'maxmindUserId',
        }
    } %}
    {% include autosuggest with {
        config: {
            label: "License Key"|t('google-maps'),
            name: 'maxmindLicenseKey',
        }
    } %}
    {% include dropdown with {
        config: {
            label: "GeoIP2 Service",
            id: 'maxmind-service',
            name: 'maxmindService',
            instructions: "Please specify which GeoIP2 Precision Web Service you have subscribed to."|t('google-maps'),
            value: settings.maxmindService ?? '',
            options: [
                { value: '',              label: '' },
                { value: 'country',       label: 'GeoIP2 Country' },
                { value: 'city',          label: 'GeoIP2 City' },
                { value: 'city_isp_org',  label: 'GeoIP2 City/ISP/Org' },
                { value: 'omni',          label: 'GeoIP2 Omni' },
            ],
        }
    } %}
</div>
